Parameter.Name: Epoch Time, TT2000, FIELDS2, Stripe Center Time
Parameter.Description: Epoch Time Tags in Terrestrial Time 2000, TT2000, Corrected Universal Time, UTC, for the FIELDS2 center time of the collected data stripe
Parameter.Caveats: This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: Telemetry Slice Number
Parameter.Description: Number of FIELDS2 100 bit per second, bps, telemetry slices in this CDF data file

Parameter.Name: Telemetry Format Version Number
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: FIELDS2 100bps Telemetry Format Version Number

Parameter.Name: Integration Duration Time
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Integration Time, the time duration for each measurement stripe

Parameter.Name: Epoch Time, TT2000, FIELDS2, Stripe Start Time
Parameter.Description: Epoch Time Tags in Terrestrial Time 2000, TT2000, Corrected Universal Time, UTC, for the stripe start time
Parameter.Caveats: This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: Epoch Time, TT2000, FIELDS2, Stripe Center Time
Parameter.Description: Epoch Time Tags in Terrestrial Time 2000, TT2000, Corrected Universal Time, UTC, for the stripe center time, this time is the same as the Epoch Time
Parameter.Caveats: This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: Epoch Time, TT2000, FIELDS2, Stripe End Time
Parameter.Description: Epoch Time Tags in Terrestrial Time 2000, TT2000, Corrected Universal Time, UTC, for the stripe end time
Parameter.Caveats: This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: Epoch Time, UNIX Format, FIELDS2, Stripe Center Time
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Epoch Time Tags in UNIX Time Format, Corrected Universal Time, UTC, for the stripe center time
Parameter.Caveats: This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: Spacecraft Mission Elapsed Time, Stripe Center Time
Parameter.Description: Spacecraft Mission Elapsed Time, MET, for the stripe center time, uncorrected
Parameter.Caveats: This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: Spacecraft Thrusting Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Spacecraft Thrusting Status Flag, indicates whether spacecraft thrusting is occuring or will occur soon

Parameter.Name: Spacecraft TWTA Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Spacecraft TWTA Status Flag, indicates whether a spacecraft traveling wave-tube amplifier, TWTA, is currently on

Parameter.Name: SCM Calibration Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: SCM Calibration Status Flag, indicates whether the internal calbration cycle of the Search Coil Magnetometer, SCM, currently is currently on

Parameter.Name: DFB Bursting Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: DFB Bursting Status Flag, indicates whether the FIELDS Digital Filter Board, DFB, is currently producing a high rate burst

Parameter.Name: FIELDS Burst Suppression Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: FIELDS Burst Suppression Status Flag, indicates whether the burst suppression flag is currently on

Parameter.Name: FIELDS Burst Suppression Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS State Change Status Flag, indicates that caution should be exercised concerning whether some aspect of the TDS configuration may have changed

Parameter.Name: FIELDS Reboot Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: FIELDS Reboot Status Flag, indicates whether the FIELDS2 processor has restarted, probably a turn-on

Parameter.Name: TDS Transition Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Transition Status Flag, indicates that caution should be exercised concerning whether some aspect of the 100 bps collection could be in transition

Parameter.Name: TDS Saturation Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Saturation Status Flag, a value of zero indicates that no TDS channels were saturated, either high or low, during the integration period. This parameter is a masking variable.

Parameter.Name: TDS High Saturation Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS High Saturation Status Flag, a value of zero indicates that no TDS channels were saturated high during the integration period. This parameter is a masking variable.

Parameter.Name: TDS Low Saturation Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Low Saturation Status Flag, a value of zero indicates that no TDS channels were saturated low during the integration period. This parameter is a masking variable.

Parameter.Name: MAGi Off Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: MAGi Off Status Flag, indicates whether the Inboard Magnetometer, MAGi, was off during the integration period

Parameter.Name: WPC Skew Off Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: WPC Skew Off Status Flag, indicates whether the Wave-Particle Correlator, WPC, skew calculation is not functioning, likely due to a lack of particles

Parameter.Name: Gap Start Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Gap Start Status Flag, indicates whether this stripe is the last before a gap in the available data

Parameter.Name: DSP LPF Status Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: DSP LPF Status Flag, indicates whether digital signal processing, DSP, low pass filtering, LPF, is in use on at least one TDS channel

Parameter.Name: TDS Analog to Digital Converter Sample Rate
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Analog to Digital Converter, ADC, Sample Rate, always equal to 1,920,000 Samples per second

Parameter.Name: TDS Down-sampling Factor
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Down-sampling Factor

Parameter.Name: TDS possibly down-sampled Sample Rate
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS possibly down-sampled Sample Rate in Samples per second

Parameter.Name: TDS Low Pass Filter Factor
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS low pass filter, LPF, Factor setting

Parameter.Name: TDS Low Pass Filter Frequency Cutoff
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS low pass filter, LPF, Frequency Cutoff, used during data collection

Parameter.Name: TDS Best Burst Flag
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Best Burst Flag, indicates that flight software, FSW, version dependent TDS burst quality values are present

Parameter.Name: TDS Best Burst Channel Number
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Best Burst Channel Number, the channel number of the TDS channel currently used for the TDS burst trigger/quality. The channel number ranges in value from 1 to 5.

Parameter.Name: TDS Best Burst Path Name
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Best Burst Path Name, signal source currently used for the TDS burst trigger/quality. This parameter is a text variable.

Parameter.Name: TDS Best Burst Quality Raw Data Quality
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Best Burst Quality Raw Data Quality, the data quality value for the best TDS burst obtained during this sample period. This parameter is expressed is expressed by using arbitrary units with larger values corresponding to higher data quality.

Parameter.Name: TDS Best Burst Q Frequency
Parameter.Set: Time Series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: TDS Best Burst Q Frequency, the frequency, or zero crossings, value observed from the best TDS burst obtained during this sample period
